# mstack core workflow

Use **separate postures** per phase. Do not plan and ship in the same breath on non-trivial work.

## Phases (order)

1. **Think** — Goal, constraints, unknowns. List **assumptions**; ask the user only for **blocking** decisions. For **non-trivial** work, optionally add a short **Model note** per `mstack-model-strategy.mdc` (suggest-only; user changes model in Cursor).
2. **Plan** — Architecture, risks, file touch list. Prefer filling `templates/PLAN_TEMPLATE.md` (or equivalent bullets in chat). For **complex or multi-file** work, use Cursor **Plan Mode**: Agent researches, asks clarifying questions, produces a **reviewable plan** before building — mode picker or **Shift+Tab** ([Plan Mode](https://cursor.com/docs/agent/plan-mode)). Save the plan to the workspace when useful so it matches this template.
3. **Build** — Minimal diff; match repo conventions; **no drive-by refactors** unless requested.
4. **Review** — Adversarial: correctness, edge cases, naming, failure modes. **No new features** in this pass.
5. **Test** — Proportionate to change; use `templates/TEST_PLAN_TEMPLATE.md` when running QA or adding tests.
6. **Ship** — Checklist: lint/tests if present, migrations, rollback, docs touchpoints. Use `templates/PR_CHECKLIST_TEMPLATE.md` when opening a PR; add an ADR (`templates/ADR_TEMPLATE.md`) if architecture changed materially. After incidents, use `templates/POSTMORTEM_TEMPLATE.md` (or `templates/INCIDENT_POSTMORTEM_TEMPLATE.md`) for a formal write-up. If new **standing** design or product preferences were explicitly agreed, update `docs/PROJECT_MEMORY.md` (or your project’s `PROJECT_MEMORY.md` path in `AGENTS.md`).
7. **Reflect** — 3–5 bullets: what worked, what to automate next time. Prefer `templates/REFLECT_TEMPLATE.md` for non-trivial work. Optional: note whether `PROJECT_MEMORY` needs updates.

## Handoff rules

- **Plan → Build**: plan must name **files/dirs** to touch and **out of scope** items.
- **Build → Review**: summarize diff intent in ≤10 lines before review.
- **Review → Test**: call out risk areas and suggested test cases.
- **Test → Ship**: list what was run vs skipped (with reason).

## When to compress phases

- Trivial one-file fixes: Think + Build + Review in one pass; still state assumptions.
- User explicitly says *quick patch only*: skip long plan template.
- **Mechanical / chore work:** `@mstack-mechanical-pass` — short inline plan; see `mstack-mechanical-pass.mdc`.

## Optional invocations

- **Plan Mode**: for ambiguous or wide-ranging tasks, use [Cursor Plan Mode](https://cursor.com/docs/agent/plan-mode) (picker or **Shift+Tab**); refine the plan before **Build**.
- **Debug mode** / *mstack debug*: follow `mstack-debug.mdc`. For runtime-heavy bugs, **prefer [Cursor Debug Mode](https://cursor.com/docs/agent/debug-mode)** (Agent mode picker or **Shift+Tab**). **Ask permission** before instrumentation or log-capture repros; use `templates/DEBUG_SESSION_TEMPLATE.md` if useful.
- **UI / UX**: follow `mstack-design-research.mdc` when gathering references; user must **permit** web research before fetching external sites.
- **Accessibility**: `@mstack-accessibility` or rely on globs in `mstack-accessibility.mdc` for component work.
- **Docs / DevEx**: `@mstack-docs-devx` when updating `README`, `docs/`, or contributor templates.
- **Data / schema**: `@mstack-data-modeling` for migrations, ORM schema, and SQL-heavy changes.
- **CI / quality**: `@mstack-ci-quality` when editing workflows or repo-wide lint/tsconfig.
- **Model / cost**: `@mstack-model-strategy` when choosing model tier, saving tokens, or using Auto—advisory only; see template `templates/MODEL_STRATEGY_NOTE_TEMPLATE.md`.
- **Session handoff**: `@mstack-session-handoff` when starting a fresh chat or parallel agent; **prefer** refreshing **`SESSION_BRIEF.md`** (repo root) from `templates/SESSION_BRIEF_TEMPLATE.md`, then open the next chat with “read `SESSION_BRIEF.md` and `docs/PROJECT_MEMORY.md`.”
- **Web perf**: rely on globs in `mstack-web-performance.mdc` or `@mstack-web-performance` for CWV and bundle work.
- **AI product** (LLM UI, tools, RAG): `@mstack-ai-product` or matching globs.
- **API contracts**: `@mstack-api-contracts` when changing public HTTP/RPC surfaces; use `templates/OPENAPI_DELTA_TEMPLATE.md` for spec deltas.
- **Observability**: `@mstack-observability` for logs, traces, metrics, correlation IDs on server paths.
- **Release / semver**: `@mstack-release-versioning` for CHANGELOG, tags, release workflows; use **`templates/RELEASE_OWNER_CHECKLIST.md`** when you own a release.
- **Secrets / env files**: `@mstack-secrets-env` when editing `.env`, CI workflows, compose, or credential paths.
- **i18n / locales** (full pack): `@mstack-i18n-localization` for catalogs and localization plumbing.
- **Project memory** (design / product prefs): `@mstack-project-memory` or globs in `mstack-project-memory.mdc`; starter `templates/PROJECT_MEMORY_TEMPLATE.md`.
- **Product review** (before large Plan): `@mstack-product-review` with `templates/PRODUCT_REVIEW_TEMPLATE.md` (big bets) or `templates/PRODUCT_REVIEW_LITE.md` (small bets) — **no code** in that posture.
- **Documentation pass** (before Ship when docs-heavy): `@mstack-documentation-pass` with `templates/DOC_TASK_TEMPLATE.md`.
- **Mechanical pass** (typos, single-file chores, obvious fixes): `@mstack-mechanical-pass` — compress phases; still follow token discipline and permissions.
- **Adoption audit** (full pack): `@mstack-adoption-audit` with **`docs/ADOPTION_AUDIT.md`** — report install gaps; no secrets/remotes changes.

